meggyjrserial.py
v0.1 1/25/2009, Joshua Ruihley
Python script to draw to Meggy Jr. RGB a grid of colors stored on web server

Understanding web service output:
Web service should serve a text file of 64 comma separated color values, 
integers in the range of 0 to 15, based on the Meggy Jr RGB Programming Guide
at http://www.evilmadscientist.com/classes/ProgrammingMeggyJr.pdf
The 64 values represent the 8 rows and 8 columns on the Meggy Jr with the 
first 8 values representing the top row, next 8 values, the second row, etc.

For an example of valid web server output, see
http://eleventy6.com/openambi/meggy_grid/getgrid.php